{"id":"330567424_MHealth_Interventions_for_Exercise_and_Risk_Factor_Modification_in_Cardiovascular_Disease","abstract":"Exercise and lifestyle risk factor management are critical for the secondary prevention of cardiovascular disease but are poorly adhered to. Mobile health interventions could enhance engagement; however, a one-size intervention approach cannot meet the needs of all people. We hypothesise a unifying digital platform that enables choice from a suite of evidence-based programs will enhance access, delivery and engagement.","authors":["Ralph Maddison","Jonathan C Rawstorn","Sheikh Mohammed Shariful Islam","Kylie Ball"],"meta":["January 2019Exercise and Sport Sciences Reviews 47(2)","DOI:10.1249/JES.0000000000000185","Project: Digital health for lifestyle and disease management"],"references":["327254915_Effects_and_costs_of_real-time_cardiac_telerehabilitation_Randomised_controlled_non-inferiority_trial","325211358_Effectiveness_of_text_message_based_diabetes_self_management_support_programme_SMS4BG_Two_arm_parallel_randomised_controlled_trial","316700179_Self-Management_Support_Using_a_Digital_Health_System_Compared_With_Usual_Care_for_Chronic_Obstructive_Pulmonary_Disease_Randomized_Controlled_Trial","313764597_The_common-sense_model_of_self-regulation_of_health_and_illness","327255847_Making_cardiac_rehabilitation_more_available_and_affordable","316823281_Self-efficacy_the_exercise_of_control","314004439_Cost-effectiveness_of_a_text_message_programme_for_the_prevention_of_recurrent_cardiovascular_events","303720845_Exercise-based_cardiac_rehabilitation_for_coronary_heart_disease","303018781_Heart_Disease_and_Stroke_Statistics-2015_Update_A_Report_from_the_American_Heart_Association","296681683_Telehealth_exercise-based_cardiac_rehabilitation_A_systematic_review_and_meta-analysis"]}